Gbenga Odogun, Lokoja The collation officer for the Igalamela/Odolu Local Government Area of Kgi State in Saturday’s governorship election said on Sunday that one unidentified person approached one of the polling units with an inducement of N50,000 to compromise the election. He told officials of the Independent National Electoral Commission at Mahmoud Yakubu Hall, venue of the collation of the governorship result in Lokoja on Sunday that the unidentified person approached one of the electoral officers and gave him the N50,000, and asked him to alter the result from the unit before submission. “The officer collected the money and I have here the money with me,” he said before giving the money to INEC officials. READ ALSO: Situation Room, NBA lament Bayelsa, Kogi polls’ violence The returning officer, Prof. Ibrahim Umar praised the collation officer and the electoral officer for demonstrating the spirit of sincerity in rejecting such offer. “You should continue to exhibit such rare behaviour; our society will one day reward you,” the returning officer said. Copyright PUNCH.
